		<div>I think druid really lack a way to heal AE. In qvic for example where mob does not hit hard but AE like crazy. A cleric can simply use group heal or even group CH. A shaman can cast their HoT on each of the ppl. HoT is very good for AE becasue AE usually has a low DPS, which is perfect for HoT which has a low HPS and HoT is very effective especially for shaman. Now for druid they have 2 choice: fast heal or CH. CH is limited by the cast time so that you cannot simply CH everyone, some must get a fast heal. Also CH is not really more effective than fast heal unless you can heal at least somewhere around 2500.<br />
<br />
In Qvic, a single cleric can handle his group, help heal the MT, while still have 30m left after the named die. 2 druids can barely hold a group, A single shaman can also hold a group if at least someone (like ranger) in group will heal himself. a druid + shaman can usualy handle the group quite well.</div>
