	<td class="alt2">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>The first thing to change is the cleric CH chain on raids. Putting druids into the chain isn't a great solution as druids would hate the job just as much as clerics. I'd say the CH chain is the most important thing to fix as it makes people quit the game. I'm sure some druids (and perhaps shaman) quit because they can't get groups (as healers) on serious content but I bet cleric burn-out is far more of a problem.<br />
<br />
If an alternative to the CH chain is found it will impact on the rest of the game and everything else will need rebalancing anyway. Who knows, druids and shaman heals might not even need altering if clerics are rebalanced properly to be more fun to play.<br />
<br />
Recently I've had an idea of 'wound counters' being applied by high end mobs along with damage. This signifies just larger bodily damage which is harder to heal, gouges instead of scratches. Healing spells would not take full effect if their were wound counters on the target player, but high level heal spells would themselves remove the wound counters. It could be made so that low level healers would struggle to remove high level wound counters, so that you needed the right level healer for the content. A 65th shaman or druid would then be a more appropriate healer for a 65th level group than a 58th cleric, which isn't always the case at the moment. Maybe complete heals wouldn't remove many wound counters so would become inappropriate for raid bosses, say. Just an idea, and it would mean a lot of content would need rebalancing <img src="http://thedruidsgrove.org/forums/images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Frown" class="inlineimg" />.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
