		<div>Trying to figure out where to put this, I think I'll put it here (and link the folks over at eqclerics, PoN and the Crucible to it).<br />
<br />
My thoughts on a "healing summit" idea, if you will, is just that, at the moment. An idea. I wanted to see if<br />
<br />
- priests had issues? (um, yeah, I'd say we all have something to say)<br />
- could talk together without killing each other (the jury's still out)<br />
<br />
I think one of a couple things could happen:<br />
<br />
A. We could start a forum here, much like Woody started a forum, and invite all the priests to come post, perhaps even invite other priest moderators to help moderate that forum (NOTE: this is off the top of my head and has not been run by Sobe - I'm just brainstorming), with STRICT forum rules on flaming, bashing, snide comments and a like (i.e., waaay above and beyond normal DG posting rules) in hopes of coming up some sort of consolidated, unified issues, ideas and possible solutions to present to SOE.<br />
<br />
B. We could let this whole new open communication post-Summit get settled in and then I present this idea to Brenlo and SOE that we have an SOE moderated forum of some sort for the same idea. (I highly doubt they will have the moderation resources for this sort of activity, but you can always ask).<br />
<br />
C. We could have representatives from each class work with their class and then the other representatives to work on stuff.<br />
<br />
<br />
Personally, I think some form of A would be best and the most doable - but, I'd like to wait a week or so before approaching Brenlo about this idea, so that things there can settle down a bit.<br />
<br />
In the meantime, by all means, please continue POLITE discussions. Flaming and snide comments don't help anyone and only make everyone grumpy. Threads like these are for construction of ideas, not destruction of people.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
