	<td class="alt2">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Divine Arbitration is an AA.  Cast time is 0.7 seconds (not instant).  It is not targeted and always works on your group.  You can't pick who gets healed and who gets hurt by it.  As mentioned, it takes all damage done in the group and evens it out.  Member1 down 3k HPs, member2 down 2k and member3 down 1k with members4-6 at full would result in member1 being healed for 2k, member2 being healed for 1k, member3 staying the same and members4-6 taking 1k damage each.  This is assuming all 3 levels of the AA were purchased.  Levels 1 and 2 add extra damage to the total before dividing.<br />
<br />
I liked the post about CH.  I'm SICK of CH.  All three priest classes have it.  Lets just kill CH.  Retune stuff that absolutely can't be done without it (as was done when mod rods where changed - there is precedent) and go on from there.  I enjoy raids much more where I'm spam healing or assist healing then when I'm counting 1 2 3 CH 2 2 3 4 3 2 3 4 4 2 3 4 5 2 3 4 1 2 3 CH for anywhere from a couple minutes to half an hour.  <br />
<br />
If there were no CH and no CH chains... both shaman and druids could get some better healing abilities and our fast cast heals might be able to be made more efficient (because we'd have nothing else to use and have to rely on them).  Rytan has mentioned he thinks HoTs should be better so maybe they could be given a lot more power - I could easily see a shaman nitch here.  Regen needs to scale up better vs mob power.  Druids and shaman wouldn't need quite as good heals if regen did more (please no one jump me - I'm not saying you shouldn't get upgrades because I think you SHOULD.  I'm just saying that IF regen were meaningful that that could be PART of the upgrade).  <br />
<br />
Stopping now cause I'm just rambling.  But I wanted to say that I think a discussion between the three classes is a great idea and I hope that people try very hard to avoid flaming.  If someone says something you don't like, debate the IDEA not the person.  A good rule of thumb... if you have to use another poster's name or refer to someone in your post then you might be making it personal and its a good idea to reread your post and think about rewording to concentrate on the IDEA and not on the person who stated the idea.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				<font color="Indigo">[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=840156">Jenarie</a> (Dark Elf) < Primal Brood > Test</font><br />
<font color="DarkOrchid">[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231627">Ariene</a> (High Elf) Bristlebane</font><br />
<font color="Plum">[62 Oracle] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=284752">Jenina</a> (Barbarian)  Bristlebane</font>
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
